.TH BLOGCRAFT 1 "October 2023" "1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
blogcraft \- A minimal static site generator
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B python blogcraft.py
[\fIcommand\fR] [\fIoptions\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B blogcraft
transforms Markdown files into a static HTML website. It features syntax highlighting, RSS feed generation, and responsive styling.
.PP
It relies on a \fBconfig.json\fR file for site-wide configuration.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B build
Compile the static website from Markdown content. This command cleans the public directory, copies assets, and renders Markdown to HTML.
.TP
.B new \fIslug\fR
Create a new article template. Creates a new content directory based on the provided \fIslug\fR with a template \fBarticle.md\fR file.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show the help message and exit.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I config.json
The main configuration file for the site settings.
.SH EXAMPLES
.B Create a new article:
.PP
.RS
$ python blogcraft.py new my-awesome-feature
.RE
.PP
.B Build the site:
.PP
.RS
$ python blogcraft.py build
.RE
